            "title": "To draw a body honestly is to say: you are worthy of being seen.",
            "heading_font_size": "heading-x-small",
            "text": "<p>Based in Jakarta, Kris draws queer, unhurried bodies in watercolour and ink. Each piece is a quiet declaration — that softness is not weakness, and that being seen is a right, not a privilege.</p><p></p>",
